Given [your comment](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75178887/configure-set-of-parameters-for-a-junit5-parameters#comment133376668_75178887):

&gt;The best outcome if I could pass no parameters (empty list/stream) or a very specific single one for a local build.

A simple solution using a system property:

```java
class SomeTest {

	static final String LOCAL_BUILD_PROPERTY = &quot;com.example.localBuild&quot;;

	@ParameterizedTest
	@MethodSource
	void test(String s) {
		System.out.println(s);
	}

	static Stream&lt;String&gt; test() {
		if (isLocalBuild()) {
			return Stream.of(&quot;single param&quot;);
		}
		return Stream.of(&quot;much&quot;, &quot;more&quot;, &quot;params&quot;);
	}

	static boolean isLocalBuild() {
		return Boolean.getBoolean(LOCAL_BUILD_PROPERTY);
	}

}
```

When you pass `-Dcom.example.localBuild=true`, only &quot;single param&quot; will be used. You can also set this property implicitly, e.g., via a [Maven profile on a specific OS](https://maven.apache.org/guides/introduction/introduction-to-profiles.html#os).

However, the &quot;problem&quot; is that the above solution doesn&#39;t report how many tests are actually skipped. A more sophisticated solution may uses a dedicated extension implementing [`InvocationInterceptor#interceptTestTemplateMethod(...)`](https://junit.org/junit5/docs/5.9.2/api/org.junit.jupiter.api/org/junit/jupiter/api/extension/InvocationInterceptor.html#interceptTestTemplateMethod(org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.InvocationInterceptor.Invocation,org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ReflectiveInvocationContext,org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtensionContext)).

@Zombies, let me show you a quick example from a script I wrote recently:

    def fetch(build, toFile) {
        new FTPClient().with {
            connect ftpServer
